message_1:
Solve the system of linear equations using Cholesky decomposition:

\begin{align*}
2x + 3y + 2z &= 11 \\
3x + 8y + 7z &= 43 \\
2x + 7y + 11z &= 49
\end{align*}

message_2:
To solve the system of linear equations using Cholesky decomposition, we first need to write the system in matrix form Ax = b, where A is the matrix of coefficients, x is the column vector of variables, and b is the column vector of constants.

A = \begin{bmatrix}
2 & 3 & 2 \\
3 & 8 & 7 \\
2 & 7 & 11
\end{bmatrix}

b = \begin{bmatrix}
11 \\
43 \\
49
\end{bmatrix}

Now, we perform Cholesky decomposition on matrix A. We decompose A into the product of a lower triangular matrix L and its transpose L^T: A = LL^T.

L = \begin{bmatrix}
l_{11} & 0 & 0 \\
l_{21} & l_{22} & 0 \\
l_{31} & l_{32} & l_{33}
\end{bmatrix}

L^T = \begin{bmatrix}
l_{11} & l_{21} & l_{31} \\
0 & l_{22} & l_{32} \\
0 & 0 & l_{33}
\end{bmatrix}

We can find the elements of L using the following equations:

l_{11} = \sqrt{a_{11}} = \sqrt{2}
l_{21} = \frac{a_{21}}{l_{11}} = \frac{3}{\sqrt{2}}
l_{31} = \frac{a_{31}}{l_{11}} = \frac{2}{\sqrt{2}}

l_{22} = \sqrt{a_{22} - l_{21}^2} = \sqrt{8 - \frac{9}{2}} = \sqrt{\frac{7}{2}}
l_{32} = \frac{a_{32} - l_{21}l_{31}}{l_{22}} = \frac{7 - \frac{6}{2}}{\sqrt{\frac{7}{2}}} = \sqrt{2}

l_{33} = \sqrt{a_{33} - l_{31}^2 - l_{32}^2} = \sqrt{11 - 2 - 2} = \sqrt{7}

So, L = \begin{bmatrix}
\sqrt{2} & 0 & 0 \\
\frac{3}{\sqrt{2}} & \sqrt{\frac{7}{2}} & 0 \\
\frac{2}{\sqrt{2}} & \sqrt{2} & \sqrt{7}
\end{bmatrix}

Now, we solve the system Ly = b for y:

\begin{bmatrix}
\sqrt{2} & 0 & 0 \\
\frac{3}{\sqrt{2}} & \sqrt{\frac{7}{2}} & 0 \\
\frac{2}{\sqrt{2}} & \sqrt{2} & \sqrt{7}
\end{bmatrix}
\begin{bmatrix}
y_1 \\
y_2 \\
y_3
\end{bmatrix} =
\begin{bmatrix}
11 \\
43 \\
49
\end{bmatrix}

Solving this system, we get:

y_1 = \frac{11}{\sqrt{2}}
y_2 = \frac{29}{\sqrt{7}}
y_3 = 3

Finally, we solve the system L^Tx = y for x:

\begin{bmatrix}
\sqrt{2} & \frac{3}{\sqrt{2}} & \frac{2}{\sqrt{2}} \\
0 & \sqrt{\frac{7}{2}} & \sqrt{2} \\
0 & 0 & \sqrt{7}
\end{bmatrix}
\begin{bmatrix}
x_1 \\
x_2 \\
x_3
\end{bmatrix} =
\begin{bmatrix}
\frac{11}{\sqrt{2}} \\
\frac{29}{\sqrt{7}} \\
3
\end{bmatrix}

Solving this system, we get:

x_1 = 1
x_2 = 2
x_3 = 3

So, the solution to the system of linear equations is x = 1, y = 2, and z = 3.
